b=\frac{\sqrt{3}-1}{2}a\quad\& \quad \frac{A-B}{2}=B\quad\&\quad\frac{A+B}{2}=2B\\\frac{a-b}{a+b}=\frac{\tan\frac{A-B}{2}}{\tan\frac{A+B}{2}}\implies \frac{3-\sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{3}+1}=\frac{\tan B}{\tan 2B}=\frac{1-\tan^2B}{2}
